What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Vegetable Shortening Market?

Market Analysis and Insights

Global Vegetable Shortening Market

Data Bridge Market Research analyses that the global vegetable shortening market to be growing at a CAGR of 5.3% in the forecast period of 2022-2029 and is likely to reach the USD 2.10 billion by 2029.

Vegetable shortenings are solid fats generated from hydrogenating vegetable oils like soybean or cotton seed oil. For baking and frying, these shortenings provide a healthier alternative to butter and lard. Vegetable shortenings have similar features to butter and lard in terms of solid texture at room temperature, but they are flavorless and odorless. A shortening is a fat that is solid at room temperature and can be used to give foods such as pastry a crisp and fresh texture. Butter, soybean, margarine, vegetable oils, and fat are all instances of fats used as shortening. The most popular vegetable oils used to make shortening are soybean, cottonseed, and refined palm oil, all of which are liquid at room temperature.

The rise in demand for bakery products among consumers will drive the vegetable shortening market. Furthermore, changing food habits of consumers and upsurge in the demand for healthy bakery ingredients are some macroeconomic factors that are positively impacting the worldwide vegetable shortening market. Another significant factor is increasing awareness about the health benefits associated with vegetable shortening will accelerate the growth rate of vegetable shortening market. The continuous change in the lifestyle of people will further expand the growth of vegetable shortening market. Other factors including strong demand from various end-use industries and growth of e-commerce platforms will increase the sales and further cushion the market’s growth rate.

Moreover, the surging demand for low calorie products among consumers will boost the beneficial opportunities for the growth of vegetable shortening market. Additionally, the rising trend of vegan food products and growing product portfolio of bakery products will act as major drivers and further create new opportunities for market’s growth in the above mentioned forecast period. The rise in product development and innovations activities will attract the consumers to opt for functional foods and beverages and hence further increase the demand for vegetable shortening market.

However, high cost associated with the product and the rising demand for clean label products from consumers will hamper the vegetable shortening market growth rate. Additionally, the presence of alternatives such as butter and lard will obstruct the vegetable shortening market's overall growth. Also, vegetable shortenings are high in trans-fat which will further pose a major challenge for the growth rate of market throughout the forecast period. The severe impact of COVID-19 on supply chain and fluctuating prices of raw materials will act as major market restrain that will further impede the growth rate of vegetable shortening market.

